<h1>BLUEPRINT FOR</br>
MUSHROOM CLOUD LA (Proximities)</h1>

<h2>The Plan</h2>
<p>
This Blueprint is an articulation of the intentions for Mushroom Cloud LA (Proximities) project (the “Project”), within an NFT environment that is evolving toward a Web 3.0 future.  Just as a blueprint for a building provides details for construction, this Blueprint is intended to embody the vision of Nancy Baker Cahill (the “Artist”) and her collaborators. This Project in its entirety is a reminder that we are not only accountable for the results of our actions, but that there is still a way by which we can consciously pull together and formulate a structure that supports life rather than continuing down a path to mutually-assured destruction.  This Blueprint and the interactivity that it contemplates, coincides with the conversations and innovation happening around efforts to connect various blockchains in a truly interoperable ecosystem.  Both this Project and the evolution of blockchain interoperability, in their own ways, reinforce the need for each of us to make use of our own networks and connections to be conduits and champions for positive and productive change.
</p>
<p>
However, building a meaningful network requires more than just intentions: it also requires action!  Recognizing the value of the artistic process beyond the initial creation of the work and the primary transaction is crucial to establishing legacy and an enduring vision. The owner of the Slipstream: Mushroom Cloud LA (Proximities) NFT (the “NFT”) is encouraged to actively engage with this Project as an innovator in an ongoing mutually-creative process, and to share the experience by circulating the NFT to as many others as possible.  With resale royalties allocated between the Artist and Wampum Codes, the Land Back/Climate Justice initiative of artist and collaborator Amelia Winger-Bearskin, every exchange provides an opportunity for the Project’s vision to be recognized anew.  The secondary transactions allow multiple Collectors to engage with the Artist, feel the sense of ownership of the artwork embedded in the NFT, and intentionally participate in advocating for environmentally sound practices.
</p>

<h2>The Details</h2>
<p>
Detail 1.	<strong>Acquiring the Work.</strong>  As soon as possible, but in any event within a reasonable time after purchasing the NFT, Collector will receive a token representing ownership of the Slipstream: Mushroom Cloud LA (Proximities) video (the “Video”).  Additionally, the primary Collector will receive a set of five (5) physical objects as further set forth in Section 3 below, and a printed copy of this Blueprint to accompany each of the five (5) objects.  Together, all of these components comprise the Project in its entirety and may be referred to as the “Artwork.”
</p>
<p>
Detail 2.	<strong>The NFT.</strong>  The NFT is minted on the Algorand blockchain.  The unique NFT is comprised of a metadata file with links on the InterPlanetary File System (IPFS) to the Video, and this Blueprint.  (The following will be revised per the description of how Uncopied will deal with the NFT and back up plans in the event of blockchain or file storage failure) [As a backup measure, upon purchase, Collectors should download the digital files associated this NFT and store the files in a secure location. In the event that any or all of the links between the NFT and the associated digital files are broken or not properly functioning, Collector still will have and can enjoy the digital files.  The NFT will remain available on the blockchain.  It is imperative that Collector save the digital files and all information pertaining to the NFT for provenance, proper recordkeeping, and any required remediation.  In the event the link(s) between the NFT and one or more of the digital files is/are broken or not properly functioning, Collector may contact Artist at info@nancybakercahillstudio.com and Artist will use reasonable efforts to remedy the situation in a fair and practicable manner.  Otherwise, Artist may elect to terminate this Agreement pursuant to the terms of Section ___ below.]
</p>
<p>
Detail 3.	<strong>The Physical Objects.</strong>  The original purchase of the unique NFT is accompanied by physical objects consisting of five (5) cubes or ‘nodes’.  Each node consists of a firey orange base, referencing the increasingly intense fire danger prominent in the Southern California location of the Project.  At the center of each cube, a single, pearlescent ‘spore’ is suspended, representing the collector’s role in supporting and ‘germinating’ a personal mycelium structure and making a meaningful contribution to an interactive community. The five (5) nodes are all 2x2 inches in size. As a physical manifestation of this Blueprint, Collector is invited to ‘gift’ four (4) of the nodes to people in their community whom Collector wishes to include in this special network.  This exercise is intended to stimulate a generative force and create an enduring network of connections beyond the Collector.
</p>
<p>
The physical artworks may be retained by the original Collector and any recipients regardless of whether the NFT is resold.  The physical artwork(s) possessed by the Collector may be resold with or without the NFT at the Collector’s discretion.  At the time of the initial sale of the NFT, the physical works will accompany this sale as a gift with purchase to be valued at their replacement value for purposes of taxes, customs, or duties calculations.  The value of the physical works for resale purposes will be based on what the market determines the value to be.
</p>
<p>
Detail 4.	<strong>Right to Display the NFT.</strong>  Collector may display the NFT for personal use, or loan the NFT for public display in an institutional setting.  Any public display of the Video must be on a square monitor, preferably with no border, and must be accompanied by the embedded sound.  The public display of the Video should include this Blueprint.  The physical objects should only be displayed in conjunction with a display of the Video and this Blueprint.
</p>
<p>
